## Anti-Patterns

| Anti-Pattern | Fix |
|---|---|
| "I assumed you wanted X" | Ask before planning |
| Vague todos | "Add POST /api/login with OAuth2" |
| Starting before approval | Always wait for confirmation |
| Over-engineering (20 todos for a toggle) | Simplicity first |
| Serial when parallel works | Launch independent agents together |
| Unclear prompts | "Implement login.ts per plan.md#todo-3" |
| Agent sprawl (10 for a simple task) | Use direct tools for simple work |

---

## Integration with Other Rules

- **Caveman:** Normal communication in planning phase, terse in execution phase
- **Security:** Mandatory security-review subagent for security-critical tasks; document threat model in planning phase
- **Karpathy Thinking:** This rule extends it ‚Äî think first, simplify, surgical changes, goal-driven verification

---

## Enforcement

**Always active.** Violations trigger correction: coding without a plan ‚Üí stop and create one. Assumptions ‚Üí stop and ask. Unclear prompts ‚Üí stop and clarify. No verification ‚Üí run tests before reporting.

**Exceptions:** User says "skip planning" or "just do it." Emergency hotfixes. Trivial changes (<5 lines, obvious fix).